claim.claim-text:
1. A computerized method for real-time activating and issuing of stored-value cards over a communications network to cardholders, the method comprising:
receiving, by a central processor, a stored-value card purchasing request received directly from a card purchaser via a respective communication gateway, and in response to receiving the card purchaser request;
communicating in real-time, by a central processor, with an unaffiliated stored-value card processing network, such network including a stored-value card processor coupled to a stored-value card database and multiple respective merchant communication devices;
communicating in real-time with a potential or existing stored-value cardholder or card purchaser regarding the stored-value card; through the card processor,
activating and issuing stored value card through the central processor to the cardholder over the Internet; and
managing the stored-value card transaction through said unaffiliated network by said central processor.

7. A method of universally managing multiple unaffiliated stored-value card processing networks, each network including a stored-value card processor connected to a stored-value card database, and multiple respective merchant communication interface devices for communication by respective merchants with said processors, said method comprising:
providing a universal central processor and communicating said processor with a universal stored-value card cardholder information database managed by said universal central processor;
communicating said universal central processor with potential or existing stored-value cardholders or holder benefactors through communication gateways,
communicating said universal central processor with said stored-value processing networks;
further programming said universal central processor for managing stored-value card transactions through said stored-value card processors.

13. A computerized system for electronically providing stored-value cards over a communications network directly to the cardholder, the system comprising:
a central information database for storing stored-value cardholder information;
a central processor for receiving card purchasing requests from respective stored-value card holders and card purchasers, said central processor coupled for communication to multiple unaffiliated stored-value card processing networks, each network including a stored-value card processor coupled to a stored value card database and multiple respective merchant communication devices, said central processor programmed in response to a card purchaser request for communicating with a respective processor to electronically activate and issue a stored-value card through the central processor over the Internet, and said central processor programmed for managing the transactions originated by a cardholder for the stored-value cards through said unaffiliated networks.
